Regulatory Compliance Solutions

EUDR:

The EUDR demands proof that the products you place on the EU market are “deforestation free” and in-line with local legislation. Our EUDR solution helps you identify and mitigate deforestation risks in your supply chain – and generate the due diligence statements that prove compliance.

  • Learn more
  • Learn more
  • Learn more

CSDDD:

The EU Corporate Sustainability Due Diligence Directive (CSDDD) comes into force in 2027 – but preparation could take up to 36 months. Our AI-powered risk monitoring and mitigation solution keeps your compliance strategy on track, providing full value chain transparency.

LkSG:

The German Supply Chain Due Diligence Act (LkSG) is Germany’s most impactful supply chain law. While reporting for the standard will soon align with the EU CSRD – and its long-term scope may be affected by CSDDD – our multi-standard solution ensures compliance today, compliance tomorrow.

Why Prewave?

1. Global Coverage

Prewave provides deep coverage on a global scale by focusing on regional, local and international sources

2. Multilingual

Prewave analyses texts in their local languages, gaining a deeper and more accurate understanding

3. Predictive

Using predictive analytics, Prewave reports on risk events before they happen

4. Machine Readable

Prewave Alerts are highly structured data points with all relevant attributes extracted

How Does Prewave Work? 1. Find and monitor your suppliers on Prewave We monitor your suppliers throughout the internet and create risk alerts for anything that impacts your suppliers. 2. Monitor your suppliers Once you receive a risk alert you can contact your supplier directly over Prewave and inquire about the suppliers status. 3. Contact your supplier Work with your supplier to resolve the issue on our Platform or assign the alert to one of your colleagues so they can get started on dealing with the problem right away. 4. Assign the tasks The whole alert can be used as a task and can be assigned to someone, for example, the responsible procurement manager who can then process the issue and take action such as finding alternative suppliers.

SCM & LOGISTICS

Prevent disruptions and understand risk
Monitor and assess the most critical elements of your supply and logistics chain for disruption risks: suppliers, transportation hubs, raw material sites, and more.

PURCHASING

Make the right decision
Evaluate suppliers based on real-life and up to date data, that doesn’t lag behind as financial and credit reports do. Be sure to have the complete picture of a supplier before you make any decision.

SUSTAINABILITY

Gain transparency into your critical stakeholders
Find out what really happens at your most important stakeholders by screening them for a broad spectrum of sustainability risks.
